cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper discusses Random Linear Network Coding (RLNC) which is a technique used in information theory and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses network coding, which is a topic in computer networks, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The paper also discusses the memory requirements of network coding, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the performance of the RLNC protocol in different network models, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses projection analysis, which is a technique used in data science and machine learning, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible category.
